main event: A UFO was sighted in Nikiski, Alaska on August 10, 1963, described as a circular object with a bluish red tail.
interesting points: The object was initially mistaken for an aircraft,The observation lasted for 2-3 minutes and was made under exceptionally clear night conditions,The object disappeared over the treeline to the southeast after the sighting, The observer used binoculars to enhance the view of the object,The case was evaluated and attributed to an aircraft landing at Kenai, Alaska.
sighted object: circular object with a bluish red tail
witness description: the observer was alone at the time of the sighting
